## ğŸ“š Real Talk: Where Do These Rules Come From?

As GRC leaders, we donâ€™t get to set the rulesâ€”we get to **align technology with them**. Today I reviewed three key sources:

### ğŸ›ï¸ 1. Laws & Regulations

- **HIPAA Security & Privacy Rules** (if handling U.S. patient data)
  - Access control
  - Audit logging
  - Encryption in transit and at rest
  - Contingency planning (backup, disaster recovery)

- **GDPR** (if in EU context)
  - Consent-based data use
  - Right to access, delete, or correct personal data

- **Local privacy laws** (e.g., Indiaâ€™s Digital Personal Data Protection Bill)

> ğŸ” *Example*: â€œEncrypt all ePHI stored in OpenMRSâ€™s MySQL database and enforce HTTPS on all endpoints.â€  
*â€” HIPAA-inspired requirement*

